:: Hack Responsible Start {"position":"725,1350","size":"100,100"}

You decide to follow responsible disclosure guidelines.  
You document everything carefully packet captures, logs, a minimal proof of concept, and a clear explanation of why this vulnerability matters. You know that medical systems are sensitive, and transparency with the vendor is the safest path.

You submit your report through Corazón’s official security disclosure channel.  
A day later, the company replies. Their message is appreciative and professional:  
they’ve reproduced the flaw, confirmed its impact, and started an internal risk assessment.

Shortly after, you receive a second email.  
Corazón invites you to participate in a Emergency meeting where you work privately with their engineers until a patch is ready, after which you may publish your research.

But there’s an ethical tension:  
Participating quietly means patient safety is prioritized.
Yet part of you wonders if being completely silent limits your visibility as a researcher.

**How do you proceed?**

• [[Fully cooperate with coordinated disclosure and prioritize patient safety.|Hack Cooperate Fully]]  
• [[Cooperate officially but still hint about your discovery publicly to build reputation.|Hack Partial Leak]]



:: Hack Sell Exploit {"position":"25,1375","size":"100,100"}
You choose profit over responsibility.  
You sell or trade the exploit through anonymous channels, receiving payment for the code you once treated as a research experiment.

But once the exploit leaves your hands, you lose all control over how it will be used.

Months later, news reports describe unexplained implant resets and targeted incidents across multiple regions.  
Investigators eventually trace the attacks back to criminal groups believed to have purchased the exploit you sold.

Corazón becomes overwhelmed: massive recalls, regulatory investigations, lawsuits, and widespread panic among patients.  
The financial and reputational damage is too great key divisions shut down, and the company begins to collapse under pressure.

